nt/page.tsx`, `app/build/roi/page.tsx`, `app/build/foundry-studio/page.tsx`, `app/build/sandbox/page.tsx`, and `app/build/page.tsx`.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T00:11:09.548Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"4p2he4u2","input":{"summary":"Performed a comprehensive motion and interaction polish pass for all 'Build With GFF' wizard tools, calculators, sandbox modules, and builders.\n\nHere is a summary of the implementation and improvements made:\n1. **Shared Workspace & Selection Polish (`components/build/components.tsx`)**:\n   - Added premium spring hover states (`whileHover={{ scale: 1.01, y: -1 }}`) and touch clicks (`whileTap={{ scale: 0.995 }}`) to all option select cards in `ToolOptionGrid`.\n   - Re-engineered `ToolSidebarProgress` with a sliding background bubble using Framer Motion's `layoutId=\"sidebarActiveBg\"`, letting the active step indicator slide smoothly as users progress.\n2. **Animated Step Transitions (`components/build/WizardStepperSystem.tsx`)**:\n   - Wrapped current step rendering content in `<AnimatePresence mode=\"wait\">` with standard slide/fade animations (`initial={{ opacity: 0, x: 8 }} animate={{ opacity: 1, x: 0 }}`) to remove sudden visual layout jumps.\n3. **Cascading Economic Waterfall Charts (`app/build/roi/page.tsx`)**:\n   - Converted standard static SVG rects into sequenced `<motion.rect>` elements that rise smoothly from the bottom baseline.\n   - Values are staggered to draw in sequentially from left to right, providing an expensive-feeling Cascade Waterfall.\n4. **Maturity Score & Radar Chart Animations (`app/build/assessment/page.tsx`)**:\n   - Converted the overall circular score ring into a `<motion.circle>` that draws its stroke dynamically via `strokeDashoffset` on load.\n   - Refactored the spider-radar polygon and outer node points to sequential spring pop-in triggers (`delay: 0.4 + idx * 0.08`), giving immediate and high-end visual feedback on diagnostic completion.\n   - Question choices are now `<motion.button>` elements that respond tactfully.\n5. **Interactive CAD Canvas Node Drift (`app/build/foundry-studio/page.tsx`)**:\n   - Replaced static positioning of the desktop `SovereignNodeCard`s on the graph canvas with `<motion.div>` cards with built-in spring transitions (`transition={{ type: \"spring\", stiffness: 280, damping: 26 }}`). Now, adding/deleting nodes or switching presets makes existing nodes drift seamlessly into their new spatial slots.\n6. **Polished Sandbox Tab Transitions (`app/build/sandbox/page.tsx`)**:\n   - Added sliding active lines (`layoutId=\"sandboxActiveTabLine\"`) to the selector tabs.\n   - Wrapped sandbox simulator detail panels in unique key-bound `<motion.div>` frames to allow rapid fluid switches.\n7. **Intelligent Guide & Selector Polish (`app/build/page.tsx`)**:\n   - Re-styled decision guide objective buttons to react with expensive, subtle hover lifts.\n\nAll pages were validated using a Next.js production compiler sweep (`next build`), compiling all 110 pages in the system with 100% success and zero TypeScript/CSS warnings.","verified":true}}}
